items.text: The old changi hokkien mee was deliciously wet with umami. Order $5 for best satisfaction.
The Fish Soup Noodles is around the corner, is super duper nice! But avoid Monday its their resting day
Duck rice !!!! Must try
The carbonara is oh so yummy! 
Pasta. Regulars to Grill & Pasta #01-34 know they can get extra cheese topping, cream or even upsize their pasta serving. Pasta noodle is on the thicker side, & sauce serving is generous!
Braised duck rice at 01-07 is solid! Friendly too.
Check out the pohpiah and curry puff here!! Great for your hi-tea !!
Satay bee hoon one of the outlet linked with Ang mo kio central hawker centre...
Fried carrot cake is the best
Stall vendors here are pretty friendly :) one guy helped me get a packet of tissues from far away cuz I spilled smtg . Besides service is excellent
Super love the pasta!! Recommend to all! :)
Try: fish soup, pasta & grill, fruit stall at the corner and coffee from sin ho huat. Dun touch the carrot cake here. Soggy and yucky. Real carrot cake lovers better give this a miss!!
Very nice prawn noodles. I had the dried one with mee kia. Soup is worth raving.
Love this food centre! Clean, windy and friendly hawkers. Delicious duck rice, carrot cake, puff, kuey tiao...
Jia jia xing pig organ soup is da bomb!!
Pig organ soup, trotters (braised or black vinegar version), braised pork ribs and yam rice at 01-10. Super duper yummy!
Seng Kee Fishball Noodles, must try!
Maggie Mee fish soup is da bomb
Tried Satay beehoon and popiah, both great! :)
Must try fish soup at the corner store! Closes on mondays !
Sin Seng Fruits are the best! Though at night only :)
Fish mee sua at corner stall is delish. Clear taste, not too salty. Generous portions of fish for $4. Nice friendly stall owner . Recommend .
The black carrot cake is delicious!
Try the char kway teow here.
The Wontan noddles at stall 1-27 is a must try! The noodles are nice and succulent!
The laksa broth was relatively thin. It was good, nonetheless.
Kway chap broth is bland. Chilli served has a weird taste.
The Kway chap here is phenomenal!
The fish soup at the corner is awesome! Though the stall closes early all the time due to exceeding demands for their generous portion of fish ^^
The vegetarian rojak is nice !
Fried hokkien mee from #01-27 is yummy!
Parking space available beside the petrol kiosk..
The fish soup in the centre stall is nicer than the one in the corner. Must try!
Kway Chap closed on Wednesday
must eat stalls include the shui kway, san ba wang guo shi (kway chap is the bomb!), tat poh chicken rice and the coffee store near toilet's awesome kaya toast (award winning!) and iced Milo!
Vegetarian options: popiah, chai tow kway, kaya toast, fruit juices, lontong, chui kway, rojak, mushroom veg noodles, curry puff
Jin Ji fishball noodles. Simply awesome
Ng tiam hwa sells the best milo and toast (sin hoe huat)
01-15. Lai Heng Fried Kway Teow. Must Try. :)
Fruit juice at front corner stall
Must tries here: cheap, good and big portion pasta! Best tasting satay bee hoon, nice char kway teow!
Grill and Pasta is the best!
Stir fried fish with Ginger from stall 01-12 is awesome
Pasta at Grill & Pasta not bad. Caters to vegetarians too
Salt water duck rice in sgp since I last tasted it in Taipei. Must try. They only open till 1-2pm and not open on Sundays.
The fish soup at the corner is overrated. Fish not bad but I find the soup bland.
Fresh fish seafood soup is GOOD. #01-36. must try. Good. ;op
Not as good as it used to be.
Sin Seng fruit stall (open only from evening) fresh and good
The salted duck noodle is worth a try as well... Must eat with the chilli!
Sin hoe Huat space bun with kaya is simply out of this world!
Sugar cane is great here!
Parking problems
Sliced Fish Soup at far right corner is best. Only one halal food stall though, food not bad. 🍛
Pig's Organ Soup is fantastic
Jing Ji fishball noodles is awesome, but open in the daytime only
The char kway teow is very good & sells lovely otah too
the chicken rice stall facing the playground is a huge disappointment...
Try the fruit juice.... Awesome n it's fresh...
Popiah & sliced fish with Maggie noodles are my faves..... Good for lunch only. Avoid mondays it is restdays for the stalls.
Bak Chor Mee from Teochew Minced Meat Noodle #01-29 was unexpectedly delicious. Noodle was slightly overcooked but ingredients were tasty. Tables around the stall were occupied by regulars
The fish soup at the corner not so awesome, soup has a lot of MSG and the thick bee hoon not properly cooked resulting very hard.
吃钣了。Lunch time
Laksa is pretty decent.
Pasta n grill n ah ee salted duck both closed. On a tuesday lunch :(
Fantastic char kuey tiao here! Friendly boss too! :)
Very tasty
Toast, eggs and kopi from 01-01 is best here!
Salted duck rice is good
Satay beehoon, 五香, sugar cane
Changi hokkien mee now here, very good
Try the salted duck at Ah Ee Traditional Hokkien Salted Duck. Give the noodles a miss tho'. (plain thick yellow noodles)
Sin Hoe Huat has the best coffee!
Popiah. Ping Kee #01-32 sees a regular stream of customers during peak hour mealtimes. Fresh ingredients & friendly, ever-smiling service are the main draw
Sliced fish soup. Many fans of Fresh Fish Seafood soup #01-36 order their bowls w Maggi noodles. I prefer mine with bee hoon or mee sua, so that amidst the blandness, taste of fish meat stands out
Try the pasta from Grill & Pasta at 01-34!
Best Kway Chap ever! Also, try the award winning kaya toast breakfast set at Sin Ho Huat!!! Uncle Ng makes the best tea + Kaya toast :D
Char kway teow is now 2nd generation. I ate it from his old man's time. Super! The sugar cane juice at the center and fruit juice at corner and poh piah are Originals since 1980s
The breakfast set (the stall near the pasta place) has good bread and comes with generous helpings of kaya and butter!
Best popiah, good cha kway tiao. Almost everything here is nice!
grill & pasta serves top notch pork chop! if not available chicken chop is a decent substitute
